        <iri>
          <value>https://cdm.ovh/rst/cons/cons#hasHeadRollingStock</value>
          <functional/>
          <inverseFunctional/>
          <annotations>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://cdm.ovh/rst/cons/cons#hasHeadRollingStock</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#label</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>has head rolling stock</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
            <annotation>
              <subject>https://cdm.ovh/rst/cons/cons#hasHeadRollingStock</subject>
              <property>http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#comment</property>
              <object>
                <lexicalForm>Each formation has exactly one "First" rolling stock. This notion of "first" is only related to the rolling stock, not however to the direction of travel which may vary (general case of multiple units or reversible trains) or not (case of hauled freight trains). Please also not that the direction of movement is yet another notion (think of shunting).</lexicalForm>
                <datatype/>
                <language>en</language>
              </object>
            </annotation>
          </annotations>
